[
 RD.POAS.JSON.CREATION.DEF

-Abstract:
 This include file contains variable definitions needed for
 PowerOn as a Service programs to use standardized
 procedures to create response JSON.

-History:
 Proj. 17.067 Release 2018.00 2/9/2018 William Morgan Original Author
 Proj. 18.016 Release 2019.00 08/08/2018 kschweers - Moved J from here to
              RD.POAS.VARIABLES.DEF.

-Details:
 The variables defined are required for the following include files:
 RD.JSON.CREATION.SET
 RD.JSON.CREATION.PRO

 This set of include files streamlines the development of PowerOn as a
 Service specfiles by providing a standardized process to create
 response JSON.

 Special characters are required to identify the beginning and the
 end of a JSON so that the Java service can extract the response
 JSON from the other messages being sent by Episys Quest.

-Dependences:
 RD.JSON.CREATION.SET
 RD.JSON.CREATION.PRO

-History:
 Proj 18.016 Release 2019.00 8/8/2018 kschweers.  Added START/CONTINUE/END tags.
]

 [ Constants ]
 POASJSONMAXJSON=9999               [ Maximum dimension of the "JSON" array    ]
 POASJSONSTARTMARK="#POAS_START#"   [ Start JSON syntax marker                 ]
 POASJSONCONTMARK="#POAS_CONTINUE#" [ Continue JSON syntax marker              ]
 POASJSONENDMARK="#POAS_END#"       [ End JSON syntax marker                   ]

 [ Variables ]
 POASJSONJ=NUMBER
 POASJSONCNTR=NUMBER
 JSON=CHARACTER ARRAY(9999)          [ Holds the JSON syntax until written     ]
 MAINOBJNAME=CHARACTER(40)
 DATAOBJNAME=CHARACTER(40)
 JSONCTR=NUMBER
 NUMHEADERFIELDS=NUMBER
 ERRORMSGCTR=NUMBER
 ERRORMSG=CHARACTER(100) ARRAY(99)
 TEMPCHAR=CHARACTER
 Q=CHARACTER(1)
 BEGINMSG=CHARACTER(1)
 ENDMSG=CHARACTER(1)
 ESCAPECHAR=CHARACTER(1)
 STATUSTYPE=CHARACTER(20)
 INPUTMESSAGEID=CHARACTER
 MSGLENGTH=NUMBER
 POASJSONFIELD=CHARACTER             [ The field name creating a JSON entry    ]
 POASJSONVALUECHAR=CHARACTER         [ A character value creating a JSON entry ]
 POASJSONVALUENUM=NUMBER             [ A number value creating a JSON entry    ]
 POASJSONVALUEMONEY=MONEY            [ A money value creating a JSON entry     ]
 POASJSONVALUERATE=RATE              [ A rate value creating a JSON entry      ]
 POASJSONVALUEDATE=DATE              [ A date value creating a JSON entry      ]
 POASJSONVALUETIME=NUMBER            [ A time value creating a JSON entry      ]
 POASJSONMESSAGE=CHARACTER(100)      [ A single message to be held in ERRORMSG ]
 POASJSONMARKER=CHARACTER            [ #CONTINUE# OR #END# marker depending    ]
